     <div type="author_to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>The Author to the Reader.</head>
   <l>I Sing the fortunes of a lucklesse payre,</l>
   <l>Whose spotlesse soules now in one body be:</l>
   <l>For beauty still is <hi>Prodromus</hi> to care,</l>
   <l>Crost by the sad starres of natiuitie;</l>
   <l>And of the strange inchauntment of a well</l>
   <l>Gi'n by the gods my sportiue Muse doth write,</l>
   <l>Which sweet-lipt <hi>Ouid</hi> long agoe did tell,</l>
   <l>Wherein who bathes, strait turnes <hi>Hermaphrodite.</hi>
   </l>
   <l>I hope my Poeme is so liuely writ,</l>
   <l>That thou wilt turne halfe-mayd with reading it.</l>
</div>
